    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-20T11:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-20T11:29:00-05:00" n="457"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1348</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Moscow</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SM1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-20T19:00:00+02:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 20, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 22, 9.55 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>279. The Patriarch of Russia has refused to sanction the peace treaty and
                    condemns same in strongest terms. American attitude will greatly influence
                    peasants especially. Inform Mr. <persName>Crane</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Summers</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
